Bootstrap: docker
From: ubuntu:22.04

%labels
    Author "Gilbert Kibet"
    Name "BBTools"
    Version "39.34"

%post
    # Update and install dependencies
    apt-get update && apt-get upgrade -y
    apt-get install -y wget openjdk-11-jre-headless tar

    # Download and install BBTools
    mkdir -p /opt
    wget -O /opt/BBMap_39.34.tar.gz https://downloads.sourceforge.net/project/bbmap/BBMap_39.34.tar.gz
    tar -xvzf /opt/BBMap_39.34.tar.gz -C /opt/
    rm /opt/BBMap_39.34.tar.gz

%environment
    export PATH=/opt/bbmap:$PATH

%runscript
    exec "$@"
%help
    Apptainer container for BBTools is an excellent suite of programs created by Brian Bushnell
    Apps available:
    bbduk.sh	BBDuk: Adapter-trimming, Contaminant/phix filtering, Quality-trimming, Quality recalibration +
    bbmap.sh	BBMap: Human/Host contaminant removal, Quality recalibration +
    bbmask.sh	BBMask: masking sequence to prevent false-positive matches in highly-conserved or low-complexity regions of genomes
    bbmerge.sh	BBMerge: Paired-read merging
    bbnorm.sh	BBNorm: Normalization, Error correction
    bbcountunique.sh	CalcUniqueness: plot the fraction of unique reads produced by a sequencing run,
    clumpify.sh	Clumpify: rapidly group overlapping reads into clumps.
    dedupe.sh	Dedupe: Deduplication to eliminate duplicate contigs in assemblies, sequences
    reformat.sh	Reformat: low memory format conversion, subsampling, filtering
    repair.sh	Repair: fix files of paired reads that became disordered
    seal.sh	Seal: “Sequence Expression AnaLyzer”. Seal is BBDuk’s sibling
    splitnextera.sh SplitNexteraLMP: Nextera LMP(long-mate-pair) library splitting
    statistics.sh    Statistics: generate assembly statistics - scaffold count, N50, L50, GC content, gap percent, etc.
    tadpole.sh	Tadpole: fast kmer-based assembler, with additional capabilities of error-correcting and extending reads.
    taxonomy.sh	Taxonomy: processing NCBI taxonomy information
    khist.sh	BBNorm: Kmer depth distribution
